The paper applies techniques from network science to map the landscape of neuroimaging research, which involves analyzing large amounts of data and creating a network of nodes and edges. This suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data analysis and machine learning techniques, which could place it in the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper also touches on topics related to psychiatry and medical applications, which could place it in the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
